title: Taft
author: Patchett, Ann
my rating: 1 of 5 stars2 of 5 stars3 of 5 stars4 of 5 stars5 of 5 starsadd to shelves
review: I picked up an Ann Patchett habit a while back, and this was the last novel I still hadn't read. Patchett always delivers on her characters, and this I picked up an Ann Patchett habit a while back, and this was the last novel I still hadn't read. Patchett always delivers on her characters, and this book is not an exception to that. But, I had a hard time figuring out what the plot was here and what it had to do with Taft. This made the good writing feel a little clumsy. Unfortunately, I also found the treatment of race to be a little off.I think I might have liked this novel better if it weren't written by Ann Patchett, which is why I'm rating it a little higher than I think I otherwise would. Ha. This wasn't a drag to get through, and as an activity I guess I did enjoy the experience of reading it! Just wish I had saved a different novel, like State of Wonder, for last....more
